(
<figureCitation id="13302A4AFFA9FF83FF038576FEDFF2BF" box="[159,287,1658,1684]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 10" captionStart-1="FIGURE 11" captionStart-2="FIGURE 12" captionStart-3="FIGURE 13" captionStart-4="FIGURE 14" captionStart-5="FIGURE 15" captionStart-6="FIGURE 16" captionStart-7="FIGURE 17" captionStartId-0="15.[151,250,1898,1922]" captionStartId-1="16.[151,250,1271,1295]" captionStartId-2="18.[151,250,1786,1810]" captionStartId-3="19.[151,250,1406,1430]" captionStartId-4="20.[151,250,1723,1747]" captionStartId-5="21.[151,250,1276,1300]" captionStartId-6="22.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionStartId-7="23.[151,250,1353,1377]" captionTargetBox-0="[161,1436,610,1863]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1436,181,1248]" captionTargetBox-2="[151,1436,381,1756]" captionTargetBox-3="[163,1416,198,1382]" captionTargetBox-4="[151,1436,633,1700]" captionTargetBox-5="[151,1429,193,1247]" captionTargetBox-6="[175,1411,479,1526]" captionTargetBox-7="[151,1437,417,1330]" captionTargetId-0="figure-211@15.[151,1436,597,1874]" captionTargetId-1="figure-19@16.[151,1436,181,1248]" captionTargetId-2="figure-100@18.[151,1436,381,1763]" captionTargetId-3="figure-27@19.[151,1436,181,1382]" captionTargetId-4="figure-196@20.[151,1436,633,1700]" captionTargetId-5="figure-27@21.[151,1436,181,1252]" captionTargetId-6="figure-166@22.[151,1435,453,1541]" captionTargetId-7="figure-143@23.[151,1437,417,1330]" captionTargetPageId-0="15" captionTargetPageId-1="16" captionTargetPageId-2="18" captionTargetPageId-3="19" captionTargetPageId-4="20" captionTargetPageId-5="21" captionTargetPageId-6="22" captionTargetPageId-7="23" captionText-0="FIGURE 10. A–B. Recently deceased female holotype V0641 of Ceroys (Miroceroys) indicattii sp. nov., from Petrópolis, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. A. Habitus in dorsal view. B. Body in dorsal, lateral and ventral view. Scale bar: 5 mm." captionText-1="FIGURE 11. A–D. Head and metathorax morphology of female Ceroys (Miroceroys) indicattii sp. nov., holotype V0641. A–C. Head; A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, ventral view. D. Metathorax in dorsal view. Abbreviations. Bs1, prothoracic basisterna; Cx, coxa; Cxp, coxopleurite; Eye, compound eye; Fc, frontal convexity; Fem, femur; Gl, glossa; Md, mandible; Mds, median segment; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Pd, pedicellus; Pgl, paraglossa; Plb, labial palpus; Pmx, maxillary palpus; Prn, pronotum; Sc, scapus; Tg, tergite. Scale bars: A–C = 0.5 mm; D = 1 mm." captionText-2="FIGURE 12. A–F. Abdomen morphology of female Ceroys (Miroceroys) indicattii sp. nov., holotype V0641, end of the abdomen: A. Dorsal view; B. Lateral view; C. Ventral view; D. Terminalia, lateral view; E. Dorsal view, detail of apex; F. Ventral view, detail of praeopercular organ. Abbreviations. Ce, cercus; Ep, epiproct; Gap8-Gap9, gonapophysis 8 and 9; Gng, gonangulum; Gpl, gonoplac; Pre, praeopercular organ; Sp, subgenital plate; St, sternite; Tg, tergite. Scale bars: 1 mm." captionText-3="FIGURE 13. A–B. Male paratype MZUSP 0529 of Ceroys (Miroceroys) indicattii sp. nov., from Teresópolis, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. A. Habitus in dorsal view. B. Body in dorsal, lateral and ventral view. Scale bar: 5 mm." captionText-4="FIGURE 14. A–D. Head and metathorax morphology of male Ceroys (Miroceroys) indicattii sp. nov., paratype MZUSP 0529. A–C. Head; A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, ventral view. D. Metathorax in dorsal view. Abbreviations. Bs1, prothoracic basisterna; Cx, coxa; Cxp, coxopleurite; Eye, compound eye; Fc, frontal convexity; Fem, femur; Md, mandible; Mds, median segment; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Pd, pedicellus; Prn, pronotum; Sc, scapus; Tg, tergite. Scale bars: A–C = 0.5 mm; D = 1 mm." captionText-5="FIGURE 15. A–E. Abdomen morphology of male Ceroys (Miroceroys) indicattii sp. nov., paratype MZUSP 0529, end of the abdomen: A. Dorsal view; B. Lateral view; D. Ventral view; E. Dorso-posterior view, detail. Abbreviations. Ce, cercus; Po, poculum; St, sternite; St9a, anterior part of sternite 9; Tg, tergite; Tp, thorn pad. Scale bars: A–C = 1 mm; D = 0.5 mm." captionText-6="FIGURE 16. A–F. Egg of Ceroys (Miroceroys) indicattii sp. nov., from the female holotype. A–B. Lateral view. C, F. Detail of micropylar plate in dorsal view. D–E. Dorsal view. Abbreviations. Mcup, micropylar cup; Mip, micropylar plate; MLi, micropylar line; Opc, operculum. Scale bars: 1 mm." captionText-7="FIGURE 17. Live habitus of the female holotype V0641 of Ceroys (Miroceroys) indicattii sp. nov., in situ when found in Petrópolis, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. Image not to scale." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531244" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531246" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531248" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531250" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531252" figureDoi-5="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531254" figureDoi-6="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531260" figureDoi-7="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531262" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6531244/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6531246/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6531248/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/6531250/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/6531252/files/figure.png" httpUri-5="https://zenodo.org/record/6531254/files/figure.png" httpUri-6="https://zenodo.org/record/6531260/files/figure.png" httpUri-7="https://zenodo.org/record/6531262/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="46">Figs 10–17</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
